\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2316286 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2316286 If Vespers is served alone, whether as daily vespers, or Great Vespers, (but not in Presanctified Liturgy, or Vesperal Liturgy, when the priest is fully vested) the priest wears only the epatrachiel, and it begin
s with the "Usual Beginning", and Psalm 102 is not sung. 
\par 
\par If Vespers is served as part of a vigil, SKIP TO PAGE
\par 
\par The priest wears the epatrachiel and phelonion, and it begins with the blessing "Glory to the Holy, Consubstantial\'85", and immediately the cler
gy sing "O Come Let Us Worship" (unless it is during Pascha), and the choir sings Psalm 103, while the priest and deacon perform the Great Ceasing, after which the priest, with bared head reads the prayers at lamplighting time in front of the royal doors.
 
\par 
\par }{\insrsid2316286 
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2316286 If Vespers is served alone (not part of a Vigil): 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2316286 
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid2316286 PRIEST: }{\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs34\insrsid2316286 Blessed is our God, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }{\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286 
\par }{\cs27\i\f1\insrsid2316286 READER: }{\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286  Amen. Glory to Thee, our God, glory to Thee.
\par 
\par O Heavenly King, Comforter, Spirit of Truth, Who art everywhere present and fillest all things, Treasury of good things and Giver of life: Come and dwell in us, and cleanse us of all impurity, and save our souls, O Good One. 
\par 
\par Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2316286 (Thrice)}{\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286 
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master, pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake. 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2316286 (Thrice)}{\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286  
\par 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par Our Father, Who art in the Heavens, hallowed by Thy Nam
e. Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done, on earth as it is in Heaven. Give us this day our daily bread, and forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors; and lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one.
\par  
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid2316286 PRIEST: }{\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs34\insrsid2316286 For Thine is the Kingdo
m, and the power, and the glory; of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.}{\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286  
\par 
\par }{\cs27\i\f1\insrsid2316286 READER: }{\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286  Amen.  Lord have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2316286 (12 Times)}{\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286 
\par 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par O come, let us worship God our King. 
\par O come, let us worship and fall down before Christ our King and God.
\par O come, let us worship and fall down before Christ Himself, our King and God. 
\par  
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\insrsid2316286 Psalm 103
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2316286 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2316286 Which is read, not sung. While the psalm is read, the priest leaves the alter and says the prayers at lamplighting time, standing with bared head in front of the royal doors. 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286 
\par Bless the Lord, O my soul; O Lord my God, Thou hast been magnified exceedingly.
\par 
\par Confession and majesty hast Thou put on, Who coverest Thyself with light as with a garment, Who stretchest out the heaven as it were a curtain; Who supporteth His chambers in the waters, Who appointeth the clouds for His ascent, Who walketh upon the wing
s of the winds, Who maketh His angels spirits, and His ministers a flame of fire, Who establisheth the earth in the sureness thereof; it shall not be turned back for ever and ever.
\par 
\par The abyss like a garment is His mantle; upon the mountains shall the waters stand.
\par 
\par At Thy rebuke they will flee, at the voice of Thy thunder shall they be afraid.
\par 
\par The mountains rise up and the plains sink down, unto the place where Thou hast established them.
\par 
\par Thou appointedst a bound that they shall not pass, neither return to cover the earth.
\par 
\par He sendeth forth springs in the valleys; between the mountains will the waters run.
\par 
\par They shall give drink to all the beasts of the field; the wild asses will wait to quench their thirst.
\par 
\par Beside them will the birds of the heaven lodge, from the midst of the rocks will they give voice.
\par 
\par He watereth the mountains from His chambers; the earth shall be satisfied with the fruit of Thy works.
\par 
\par He causeth the grass to grow for the cattle, and green herb for the service of men, To bring forth bread out of the earth; and wine maketh glad the heart of man.
\par 
\par To make his face cheerful with oil; and bread strengtheneth man's heart.
\par 
\par The trees of the plain shall be satisfied, the cedars of Lebanon, which Thou hast planted.
\par 
\par There will the sparrows make their nests; the house of the heron is chief among them.
\par 
\par The high mountains are a refuge for the harts, and so is the rock for the hares.
\par 
\par He hath made the moon for seasons; the sun knoweth his going down.
\par 
\par Thou appointedst the darkness, and there was the night, wherein all the beasts of the forest will go abroad.
\par 
\par Young lions roaring after their prey, and seeking their food from God.
\par 
\par The sun ariseth, and they are gathered together, and they lay them down in their dens.
\par 
\par But man shall go forth unto his work, and to his labour until the evening.
\par 
\par How magnified are Thy works, O Lord! In wisdom hast Thou made them all; the earth is filled with Thy creation.
\par 
\par So is this great and spacious sea, therein are things creeping innumerable, small living creatures with the great.
\par 
\par There go the ships; there this dragon, whom Thou hast made to play therein.
\par 
\par All things wait on Thee, to give them their food in due season; when Thou givest it them, they will gather it.
\par 
\par When Thou openest Thy hand, all things shall be filled with goodness; when Thou turnest away Thy face, they shall be troubled.
\par 
\par Thou wilt take their spirit, and they shall cease; and unto their dust shall they return.
\par 
\par Thou wilt send forth Thy Spirit, and they shall be created; and Thou shalt renew the face of the earth.
\par 
\par Let the glory of the Lord be unto the ages; the Lord will rejoice in His works.
\par 
\par Who looketh on the earth and maketh it tremble, Who toucheth the mountains and they smoke.
\par 
\par I will sing unto the Lord throughout my life, I will chant to my God for as long as I have my being.
\par 
\par May my words be sweet unto Him, and I will rejoice in the Lord.
\par 
\par O that sinners would cease from the earth, and they that work iniquity, that they should be no more.
\par 
\par Bless the Lord, O my soul.
\par 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to thee, O God.
\par Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to thee, O God.
\par Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to thee, O God.
\par 
\par O our God and our Hope, glory to thee.
\par 
\par }{\insrsid2316286 
\par }{\cs49\b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\insrsid2316286 Immediately following, the Great Litany is intoned by the priest (or deacon, standing before the royal doors. 
\par SKIP TO PAGE
