\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid2316286 Choir:}{\insrsid2316286  }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2316286 Blessed is the man that hath not walked in the counsel of the ungodly. Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia.
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs42\i\f1\fs24\insrsid2316286 
\par Reader: }{\cs41\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286 nor stood in the way of sinners, nor sat in the seat of the pestilent. 
\par 
\par But his will is rather in the law of the Lord, and in His law will he meditate day and night. 
\par 
\par And he shall be like the tree which is planted by the streams of the waters, which shall bring forth its fruit in its season; and its leaf shall not fall, and all things whatsoever he may do shall prosper. 
\par 
\par Not so are the ungodly, not so; but rather they are like the chaff which the wind doth hurl away from the face of the earth. 
\par 
\par For this reason shall the ungodly not stand up in judgement, nor sinners in the council of the righteous.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid2316286 
\par Choir:}{\insrsid2316286  }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2316286 For the Lord knoweth the way of the righteous, and the way of the ungodly shall perish. Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia.
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs42\i\f1\fs24\insrsid2316286 
\par Reader:}{\insrsid2316286  }{\cs41\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286 Why have the heathen raged, and the peoples meditated empty things? 
\par 
\par The kings of the earth were aroused, and the rulers were assembled together, against the Lord, and against His Christ. 
\par Let us break their bonds asunder, and let us cast away their yoke from us. 
\par 
\par He that dwelleth in the heavens shall laugh them to scorn, and the Lord shall deride them. 
\par 
\par Then shall He speak unto them in His wrath, and in His anger shall He trouble them. 
\par 
\par But as for Me, I was established as king by Him, upon Sion His holy mountain, proclaiming the commandment of the Lord. 
\par The Lord said unto Me: Thou art My Son, this day have I begotten Thee. 
\par 
\par Ask of Me, and I will give Thee the nations for Thine inheritance, and the uttermost parts of the earth for Thy possession. 
\par 
\par Thou shalt herd them with a rod of iron; Thou shalt shatter them like a potter's vessels. 
\par 
\par And now, O ye kings, understand; be instructed, all ye that judge the earth.}{\insrsid2316286 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid2316286 
\par Choir:}{\b\i\insrsid2316286  }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2316286 Serve ye the Lord with fear, and rejoice in Him with trembling. Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia.
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs42\i\f1\fs24\insrsid2316286 
\par Reader:}{\insrsid2316286  }{\cs41\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286 Lay hold of instruction, lest at any time the Lord be angry, and ye perish from the righteous way. 
\par When quickly His wrath be kindled,}{\insrsid2316286 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid2316286 
\par Choir:}{\b\i\insrsid2316286  }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2316286 Blessed are all that have put their trust in Him. Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia}{\insrsid2316286 .
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs42\i\f1\fs24\insrsid2316286 
\par Reader:}{\insrsid2316286  }{\cs41\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286 O Lord, why are they multiplied that afflict me? Many rise up against me. 
\par 
\par Many say unto my soul: There is no salvation for him in his God. 
\par But Thou, O Lord, art my helper, my glory, and the lifter up of my head. 
\par 
\par mountain. 
\par 
\par I laid me down and slept; I awoke, for the Lord will help me. 
\par I will not be afraid of ten thousands of people that set themselves against me round about.
\par }{\insrsid2316286 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid2316286 Choir:}{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2316286  Arise, O Lord, save me, O my God. Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia.
\par }{\cs42\i\f1\fs24\insrsid2316286 
\par Reader:}{\b\i\insrsid2316286  }{\cs41\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286 for Thou hast smitten all who without cause are mine enemies; the teeth of sinners hast Thou broken.
\par }{\insrsid2316286 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid2316286 Choir:}{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2316286  Salvation is of the Lord, and Thy blessing is upon Thy people. Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia.
\par }{\insrsid2316286 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28\cf15\insrsid2316286 Choir:}{\b\i\insrsid2316286  }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2316286 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to Thee, O God. 
\par Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to Thee, O God. 
\par Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to Thee, O God.  
