\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs41\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286 Unto my words, give ear, O Lord; hear my cry. 
\par 
\par Attend unto the voice of my supplication, O my King and my God; for unto Thee will I pray, O Lord. 
\par 
\par In the morning Thou shalt hear my voice. 
\par 
\par In the morning shall I stand before Thee, and Thou shalt look upon me; for not a God that willest iniquity art Thou. 
\par 
\par He that worketh evil shall not dwell near Thee, nor shall transgressors abide before Thine eyes.
\par  
\par Thou hast hated all them that work iniquity; Thou shalt destroy all them that speak a lie. 
\par 
\par A man that is bloody and deceitful shall the Lord abhor. 
\par 
\par But as for me, in the multitude of Thy mercy shall I go into Thy house; I shall worship toward Thy holy temple in fear of Thee. 
\par 
\par O Lord, guide me in the way of Thy righteousness; because of mine enemies, make straight my way before Thee. 
\par 
\par For in their mouth there is no truth; their heart is vain.
\par  
\par Their throat is an open sepulchre, with their tongues have they spoken deceitfully; judge them, O God. 
\par 
\par Let them fall down on account of their own devisings; according to the multitude of their ungodliness, cast them out, for they have embittered Thee, O Lord. 
\par 
\par And let all them be glad that hope in Thee; they shall ever rejoice, and Thou shalt dwell among them. 
\par 
\par And all shall glory in Thee that love Thy name, for Thou shalt bless the righteous. 
\par 
\par O Lord, as with a shield of Thy good pleasure hast Thou crowned us.}{\insrsid2316286  
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs38\insrsid2316286 \page PSALM 6}{\cs38\i0\insrsid2316286  
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid2316286 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs41\f1\fs32\insrsid2316286 O Lord, rebuke me not in Thine anger, nor chasten me in Thy wrath. 
\par Have mercy on me, O Lord, for I am weak. 
\par 
\par Heal me, O Lord, for my bones are troubled, and my soul is troubled greatly; but Thou, O Lord, how long? 
\par 
\par Turn to me again, O Lord, deliver my soul; save me for Thy mercy's sake. 
\par 
\par For in death there is none that is mindful of Thee, and in hades who will confess Thee? 
\par 
\par I toiled in my groaning; every night I will wash my bed, with tears will I water my couch. 
\par 
\par Through wrath is mine eye become troubled, I have grown old among all mine enemies. 
\par 
\par Depart from me all ye that work vanity, for the Lord hath heard the voice of my weeping.
\par  
\par The Lord hath heard my supplication, the Lord hath received my prayer. 
\par 
\par Let all mine enemies be greatly put to shame and be troubled, let them be turned back, and speedily be greatly put to shame. 
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to Thee, O God. 
\par Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to Thee, O God. 
\par Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to Thee, O God. 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs38\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2316286 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj {\footer \pard\plain \s34\qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tqc\tx4320\tqr\tx8640\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
